---
---

<section class="km-section--base relative reveal-on-scroll">
  <div class="km-divider"></div>
  <div class="km-container" style="padding-top: var(--km-section-py); padding-bottom: var(--km-section-py);">
    <div class="text-center max-w-[700px] mx-auto mb-16">
      <p class="km-label">The Problem</p>
      <h2 class="km-heading text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,3rem)]">
        You're spending thousands on Kubernetes. But do you know what each workload actually costs?
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <!-- Card 1 -->
      <div class="km-card km-card--glow km-card--tracked km-stagger p-7 md:p-8 group relative overflow-hidden" style="--i:0">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-[#10b981]/8 border border-[#10b981]/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:border-[#10b981]/25 transition-colors relative z-10">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#10b981" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="opacity-70">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
            <line x1="4" y1="4" x2="20" y2="20"></line>
            <path d="M12 8v4M12 16h.01"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-[1.1rem] font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight relative z-10">No Per-Container Visibility</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.875rem] text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed relative z-10">
          AWS Cost Explorer shows you EC2 bills. Kubecost estimates pod costs. Neither tells you what a single container actually consumes in energy and compute — the real drivers of your bill.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2 -->
      <div class="km-card km-card--glow km-card--tracked km-stagger p-7 md:p-8 group relative overflow-hidden" style="--i:1">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-[#10b981]/8 border border-[#10b981]/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:border-[#10b981]/25 transition-colors relative z-10">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#10b981" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="opacity-70">
            <rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="18" rx="2"></rect>
            <path d="M7 8h10M7 12h6M7 16h8"></path>
            <path d="M17 14l3 3-3 3" opacity="0.5"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-[1.1rem] font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight relative z-10">Overprovisioned and Flying Blind</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.875rem] text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed relative z-10">
          Most teams request 2-4x the resources their workloads actually use. Without per-workload waste detection, you're paying for idle CPU and memory every hour of every day.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3 -->
      <div class="km-card km-card--glow km-card--tracked km-stagger p-7 md:p-8 group relative overflow-hidden" style="--i:2">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-[#10b981]/8 border border-[#10b981]/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:border-[#10b981]/25 transition-colors relative z-10">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#10b981" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="opacity-70">
            <polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"></polyline>
            <polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-[1.1rem] font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight relative z-10">Deploys Make It Worse (Silently)</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.875rem] text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed relative z-10">
          You ship a new image version. CPU goes up 15%. Memory creeps up. Nobody notices because no tool tracks efficiency changes between deployments. The waste compounds with every release.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
